cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to anticipate human actions and objects in videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques to predict visual representations, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of unlabeled video data, which is a common topic in the field of unsupervised learning, falling under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of recognition algorithms, which is a topic in multimedia processing, falling under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses deep networks to predict future visual representations, which is a topic in neural networks, falling under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
